  "business_context": "Payment records track money received. Each payment has an amount and a method (credit card, ACH, check, cash, wire, in-kind), a date, and some target it's being applied against — typically an Invoice (in commerce contexts), a Donation / Contribution (in nonprofit donation contexts), or a Pledge (in nonprofit pledge-payment contexts). Payment-to-target modeling is the most divergent aspect: a single payment may apply to a single invoice, to multiple invoices (split-payment), or to a single donation. Payments connect the CRM to the financial system — most CRM Payment objects are reflections of records that live authoritatively in the payment processor (Stripe, Authorize.net, Braintree) or accounting system. NPSP separates Donation (Opportunity) from Payment via the npe01__OppPayment__c custom object — a Donation can be paid via multiple Payment records representing pledge installments. Bloomerang has Transaction (which is often used for already-received payments) plus separate Pledge entities for pledged-but-unpaid commitments. CiviCRM has Contribution (the donation/transaction) plus separate Payment records that apply against Contributions to handle partial payments. When interviewing clients, surface \"Payment\" by asking how they receive money: one-time donations, recurring billing, pledges paid in installments, sales orders paid on invoice. Different patterns require different Payment modeling depth.",
